64
00:03:08.255 --> 00:03:11.425 line:-2 align:center
In this session,
we will cover three topics.


65
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:16,530 line:-2
First, App Clip Card in Safari
and SafariViewController.


66
00:03:16.563 --> 00:03:21.835 line:-2 align:center
Then, we will talk about testing
App Clip with local experiences.


67
00:03:21.869 --> 00:03:25.305 line:-2 align:center
Last, we will cover
App Clip code.


68
00:03:27.341 --> 00:03:31.345 line:-2 align:center
Let's look at a new way
to explore App Clips.


69
00:03:31.378 --> 00:03:34.848 line:-2 align:center
Your website can use
apple-itunes-app meta tag


70
00:03:34.882 --> 00:03:36.650 line:-1 align:center
to display the smart app banner


71
00:03:36.683 --> 00:03:39.419 line:-2 align:center
in Safari
or Safari View Controller.


72
00:03:39.453 --> 00:03:43.123 line:-2 align:center
In iOS 15, you can configure
the meta tag to show


73
00:03:43,156 --> 00:03:47,694 line:-2
a full-sized App Clip Card,
right in the middle of web page.


74
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:50,998 line:-2
User can
open your App Clip from there.


75
00:03:51,031 --> 00:03:54,868 line:-2
If they choose "View in Safari,"
Safari will remember the choice


76
00:03:54.902 --> 00:03:57.604 line:-2 align:center
and not show the card next time
the page is loaded again.


77
00:03:57,638 --> 00:04:01,675 line:-2
And it will fall back
to the original banner.


78
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:03,777 line:-1
To opt-in card mode,


79
00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:06,513 line:-2
you just need to add
"app-clip-display" key


80
00:04:06.547 --> 00:04:10.784 line:-2 align:center
to the meta tag
and set it to "card."


81
00:04:10.817 --> 00:04:13.053 line:-1 align:center
The card mode works great


82
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:16,190 line:-2
if you like to promote
your App Clip in the web page.


83
00:04:16,223 --> 00:04:18,425 line:-2
For apps
using SafariViewController


84
00:04:18.458 --> 00:04:20.861 line:-2 align:center
to render web content,
like Twitter,


85
00:04:20.894 --> 00:04:24.264 line:-2 align:center
it can show the card
as a part of the app's UI.


86
00:04:24,298 --> 00:04:26,300 line:-2
Now, user
can launch the App Clip


87
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,702 line:-1
directly from the app.


88
00:04:33,006 --> 00:04:35,142 line:-2
This is the App Clip Card
in Safari


89
00:04:35,175 --> 00:04:37,611 line:-1
and SafariViewController.


90
00:04:37,644 --> 00:04:42,015 line:-2
Let's talk about test
with local experiences.


91
00:04:42,049 --> 00:04:44,852 line:-2
For users,
their App Clip experience


92
00:04:44,885 --> 00:04:48,388 line:-1
starts with the App Clip Card.


93
00:04:48.422 --> 00:04:51.725 line:-2 align:center
The card shows your App Clip's
title, subtitle,


94
00:04:51,758 --> 00:04:54,294 line:-2
what action can take,
and a header image


95
00:04:54,328 --> 00:04:56,864 line:-1
to show your brand and style.


96
00:04:56,897 --> 00:05:00,100 line:-2
You can create an App Clip Card
in App Store Connect.


97
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:03,737 line:-2
Follow the step-by-step guide
to configure all the elements.


98
00:05:03.770 --> 00:05:07.708 line:-2 align:center
You can also specify locations
associated with your App Clip.


99
00:05:07.741 --> 00:05:11.078 line:-2 align:center
This could make the App Clip
show up in Maps place card,


100
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:16,283 line:-2
Siri suggestion widget,
or Spotlight search.


101
00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:20.320 line:-2 align:center
To know about how to customize
App Clip Card, please refer


102
00:05:20,354 --> 00:05:24,157 line:-2
to WWDC20 sessions, "What's
new in App Store Connect"


103
00:05:24,191 --> 00:05:26,960 line:-2
and "Configure
and link your App Clips."


104
00:05:26.994 --> 00:05:29.830 line:-2 align:center
Now, when you develop
your App Clip, you might


105
00:05:29.863 --> 00:05:33.200 line:-2 align:center
not have registered
any App Clip experiences yet.


106
00:05:33.233 --> 00:05:35.969 line:-2 align:center
Sometimes, you do want
to test the end-to-end flow


107
00:05:36,003 --> 00:05:38,172 line:-2
and role-play
the whole experience.


108
00:05:38,205 --> 00:05:41,175 line:-2
You can do
that with local experiences.


109
00:05:41.208 --> 00:05:44.077 line:-2 align:center
A local experience is
an experience you enter


110
00:05:44.111 --> 00:05:46.146 line:-1 align:center
in your own testing device.


111
00:05:46.180 --> 00:05:47.714 line:-1 align:center
You can launch it with most


112
00:05:47,748 --> 00:05:51,451 line:-2
of regular
App Clip invocation methods.


113
00:05:51.485 --> 00:05:54.788 line:-2 align:center
To create a local experience,
go to Developer Settings


114
00:05:54.821 --> 00:05:57.858 line:-1 align:center
and select Local Experiences.


115
00:05:57.891 --> 00:06:01.628 line:-2 align:center
Specify your App Clip's name,
title, URL prefix,


116
00:06:01,662 --> 00:06:03,830 line:-1
bundleID, and select an image


117
00:06:03.864 --> 00:06:06.900 line:-2 align:center
in your photo library
as the header image.


118
00:06:06.934 --> 00:06:10.003 line:-2 align:center
You can then scan
a QR code or NFC tag


119
00:06:10.037 --> 00:06:12.206 line:-1 align:center
to launch the experience.


120
00:06:12.239 --> 00:06:16.343 line:-2 align:center
Local experiences support QR,
NFC, App Clip Code,


121
00:06:16.376 --> 00:06:18.412 line:-1 align:center
Safari, and Messages.


122
00:06:18.445 --> 00:06:19.980 line:-1 align:center
They don't show up in Maps,


123
00:06:20.013 --> 00:06:23.250 line:-2 align:center
location suggestions,
and Spotlight search.


124
00:06:23,283 --> 00:06:26,186 line:-2
These require
registered experiences.


125
00:06:26.220 --> 00:06:29.223 line:-2 align:center
Also, you can only
specify local experiences


126
00:06:29.256 --> 00:06:33.427 line:-2 align:center
for Xcode-installed App Clips
or App Clips in Beta testing.


127
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:36,864 line:-2
This is how you can test
with local experiences.


128
00:06:36.897 --> 00:06:38.799 line:-2 align:center
With that, I would like
to hand over


129
00:06:38.832 --> 00:06:41.034 line:-1 align:center
to Luming to show you a demo.


