167
00:08:36.517 --> 00:08:38.385 line:-2 align:center
Now, I know
how to launch my App Clip


168
00:08:38,418 --> 00:08:41,788 line:-2
from the app with the help
of SFSafariViewController.


169
00:08:41.822 --> 00:08:45.025 line:-2 align:center
Now, let's talk
about App Clip code.


170
00:08:45,058 --> 00:08:48,662 line:-2
App Clip code is a new,
Apple-designed visual code.


171
00:08:48.695 --> 00:08:51.832 line:-2 align:center
It is the best way
to discover App Clip experiences


172
00:08:51,865 --> 00:08:53,534 line:-1
in the real world.


173
00:08:53,567 --> 00:08:57,004 line:-1
It is available from iOS 14.3.


174
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:59,373 line:-2
So, there are
almost 1 billion devices ready


175
00:08:59,406 --> 00:09:01,642 line:-1
for your App Clip code.


176
00:09:01.675 --> 00:09:05.612 line:-2 align:center
An App Clip code always leads
to an App Clip.


177
00:09:05.646 --> 00:09:07.614 line:-1 align:center
When the user sees such a code,


178
00:09:07,648 --> 00:09:11,285 line:-2
they know there's an App Clip
to explore.


179
00:09:11.318 --> 00:09:15.656 line:-2 align:center
Each code encodes a unique URL
for specific experience.


180
00:09:15.689 --> 00:09:19.226 line:-2 align:center
iOS decodes the URL
before sending to the App Clip.


181
00:09:19,259 --> 00:09:21,595 line:-2
This means your App Clip
doesn't need


182
00:09:21.628 --> 00:09:24.264 line:-2 align:center
to do anything special
to handle these codes.


183
00:09:24,298 --> 00:09:28,836 line:-2
Your existing URL handling
will just work.


184
00:09:28.869 --> 00:09:31.238 line:-2 align:center
There are two types
of App Clip code:


185
00:09:31,271 --> 00:09:34,274 line:-1
NFC integrated or Scan only.


186
00:09:34,308 --> 00:09:37,144 line:-2
User can interact
with NFC-integrated code


187
00:09:37.177 --> 00:09:39.880 line:-2 align:center
by tap it or scanning it
with the camera.


188
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:43,450 line:-2
Use this type when customer
can easily access the code.


189
00:09:43.483 --> 00:09:45.586 line:-2 align:center
For example,
on a vending machine,


190
00:09:45,619 --> 00:09:49,690 line:-2
or on a restaurant table,
or on storefront window.


191
00:09:49.723 --> 00:09:53.527 line:-2 align:center
Use scan only if the code
may be placed out of reach


192
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:57,664 line:-2
for the customer,
or when NFC is not appropriate.


193
00:09:57.698 --> 00:10:00.901 line:-2 align:center
For example,
when it is displayed digitally


194
00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:04.538 line:-1 align:center
in a marketing email.


195
00:10:04.571 --> 00:10:07.241 line:-2 align:center
You can customize
the style of App Clip code


196
00:10:07.274 --> 00:10:09.910 line:-1 align:center
to fit specific use cases.


197
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:13,213 line:-2
You can pick you own foreground
or background color.


198
00:10:13.247 --> 00:10:15.849 line:-2 align:center
You can also
hide the App Clip logo.


199
00:10:15.883 --> 00:10:19.319 line:-2 align:center
We suggest to show the logo
when there is enough space.


200
00:10:19,353 --> 00:10:22,189 line:-2
This gives new customer
a clear message


201
00:10:22.222 --> 00:10:24.858 line:-1 align:center
that it is for App Clips.


202
00:10:24.892 --> 00:10:27.461 line:-1 align:center
If you have an ARKit App Clip,


203
00:10:27.494 --> 00:10:29.997 line:-2 align:center
you can use App Clip code
as an anchor,


204
00:10:30.030 --> 00:10:32.933 line:-2 align:center
tracking its position
in the physical world.


205
00:10:32.966 --> 00:10:35.402 line:-2 align:center
This could
bring amazing experiences.


206
00:10:35.435 --> 00:10:37.871 line:-2 align:center
For example,
a user can scan an App Clip code


207
00:10:37,905 --> 00:10:40,507 line:-2
on a package,
exploring what is inside,


208
00:10:40,541 --> 00:10:44,778 line:-2
like this guitar,
without opening the package.


209
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:47,748 line:-2
To know more
about App Clip code and ARKit,


210
00:10:47.781 --> 00:10:53.754 line:-2 align:center
please check out WWDC21 session,
"Explore ARKit 5."


211
00:10:53.787 --> 00:10:56.356 line:-2 align:center
There are two ways
to create an App Clip code.


212
00:10:56.390 --> 00:10:58.859 line:-2 align:center
You can use
the App Clip Code Generator tool,


213
00:10:58.892 --> 00:11:01.628 line:-2 align:center
available
from developer.apple.com,


214
00:11:01.662 --> 00:11:06.767 line:-2 align:center
or you can download the code
directly from App Store Connect.


215
00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:09.303 line:-2 align:center
We recommend
to use the command-line tool


216
00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:11.939 line:-2 align:center
when you're testing
or developing an App Clip,


217
00:11:11,972 --> 00:11:15,475 line:-2
or you need
to automate code generation.


218
00:11:15.509 --> 00:11:20.380 line:-2 align:center
Use App Store Connect to create
codes for registered URLs.


219
00:11:20,414 --> 00:11:22,349 line:-2
For the best scanning
experience,


220
00:11:22,382 --> 00:11:24,484 line:-2
here are some guidelines
to keep in mind.


221
00:11:24.518 --> 00:11:28.322 line:-2 align:center
First, keep the code
on a flat surface.


222
00:11:28,355 --> 00:11:31,391 line:-2
The code should be placed
at upright position.


223
00:11:31,425 --> 00:11:36,063 line:-2
Make sure you don't rotate
the code or the central logo.


224
00:11:36,096 --> 00:11:40,167 line:-2
Small codes are harder
for customers to see and scan,


225
00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:45.205 line:-2 align:center
so make sure your code is large
enough, at least 1 inch wide.


226
00:11:46,807 --> 00:11:48,775 line:-1
Ensure good visibility.


227
00:11:48,809 --> 00:11:51,612 line:-2
Make sure your code is
not blocked, damaged,


228
00:11:51,645 --> 00:11:56,149 line:-2
or placed too close
to other codes.


229
00:11:56,183 --> 00:11:59,253 line:-2
You can add a text next
to the code to inform people


230
00:11:59.286 --> 00:12:02.122 line:-2 align:center
how they can use it
to launch your App Clip.


231
00:12:02,155 --> 00:12:07,127 line:-2
Make sure the message is concise
and with a clear call to action.


232
00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:09.396 line:-2 align:center
For more information,
please check


233
00:12:09.429 --> 00:12:14.268 line:-2 align:center
the Human Interface Guidelines
and This is App Clip Code.


